**Clinical Reasoning:**
All patients with secondary amenorrhea must have pregnancy ruled out initially, regardless of hormonal profile. Even though elevated LH/FSH suggest hypergonadotropic hypogonadism, pregnancy remains a critical differentiator—especially since some forms of amenorrhea (like early pregnancy) mimic hormonal disturbances. Thus, the next best step is to check urine HCG.

